                <div class="questionnaires-tutorial">					
                    <div class="questionnaires-section">
                        <h1 class="tutorial-heading">Screening Questionnaires Tutorial</h1>
                        <div class="tutorial-text">
                            <p>The Screening Questionnaires is a feature that allows employers to create a Questionnaire with a pass/fail scoring system.
                                Employers can also add the Questionnaire to any Job Posting to filter candidates according to their answers.
                                Job Seekers when applying for a position, are required to answer the questionnaire in order to complete the application process.</p>
                        </div>
                        <h1 id="new-questionnaire" class="tutorial-heading">Creating a New Questionnaire</h1>
                        <div class="tutorial-text">
                            <p>To create a new questionnaire an employer should go to the<br>Dashboard >> and click on the Questionnaires menu icon:</p>
                            <img src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-1-new.jpg">
                            <p>Then on the opened page click on the "Create New Questionnaire" Button:</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-2-new.jpg">
                            <p>Enter a desired Name for the Questionnaire and specify, a needed Passing Score to filter candidates according to their answers:</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-3-new.jpg">
                            <p>Under the 'Passing Score' section an employer can select the settings for sending an auto-reply ('pass/fail') email message to candidates.</p>
                            <img src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-4-new.jpg">
                            <p>To enable auto-reply Pass/Fail email messages to be sent to one or both types of candidates an employer should check the box(es).There will be a text area displayed, where an employer can insert a desired email text to be sent to this particular type of cadidate:</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-5-new.jpg">
                            <p>Once all settings are made an employer needs to press the "Submit" button at the bottom of the page in order to add a new Questionnaire.</p>
                            <p>A newly created Questionnaire will appear in a table on the same page below:<br><img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-9-new.jpg"></p>
                        </div>
                        <h1 id="questions-to-questionnaire" class="tutorial-heading">Adding Questions to a Questionnaire</h1>
                        <div class="tutorial-text">
                            <p>After an employer has created a Questionnaire, they can proceed to adding questions by clicking on the "Manage Question" button. A new screen will appear. Click on the "ADD NEW QUESTION" button.</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-10-new.jpg">
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-6-new.jpg">
                            <p><strong>Question</strong> -an employer enters a Question</p>
                            <p><strong>Required -</strong> If the employer would like this question to be a 'required' answer then place a check this box.</p>
                            <p><strong>Answer Type -</strong> Employers are given multiple format options for the type of answer they are looking for.</p>
                            <p>To add a new question an employer simply needs to enter Question name, set an Answer Type and press the "Add" button.</p>
                            <p>"<strong><em>Text</em></strong>" type - Job seekers will be given a text area to enter their answer to this question;</p>
                            <p>"<strong><em>Yes/No</em></strong>" type - Job seekers will be able to select a 'yes' or 'no' answer. An employer can set a score for each answer.</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-7-new.jpg">
                            <p>"<strong><em>List of answers with multiple choice</em></strong>" type - Job seekers will be able to choose from one or more of the answers preset by an employer.<br> Each answer may have different score:</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-8-new.jpg">
                            <p>"<strong><em>List of answers with single choice</em></strong>" type - is set in the same way as the previous type described above. The only difference is that job seekers will be able to choose from only one answer.</p>
                            <p>A newly created Question will appear in a table on the same page below:<br><img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-15-new.jpg"></p>
                        </div>
                        <h1 id="questions-to-job" class="tutorial-heading">Adding a Questionnaire to a Job Posting</h1>
                        <div class="tutorial-text">
                            <p>To add a Questionnaire to a certain Job posting an employer needs to go to Dashboard &gt;&gt; My Jobs menu and edit the needed Job posting.</p>
                            <p>At the bottom of the "Edit Listing" page there is a "Screening Questionnaire" section:</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-12-new.jpg">
                            <p>There an employer needs to select a Questionnaire to be added to this Job posting and then press the "Save" button.</p>
                            <p><strong>Note:&nbsp; </strong>an employer can add only one Questionnaire for a certain Job posting.</p>
                        </div>
                        <h1 id="questions-to-applynow-form" class="tutorial-heading">Screening Questionnaire on the Apply Now form</h1>
                        <div class="tutorial-text">
                            <p>A Screening Questionnaire added to a certain Job posting will be displayed on the "Apply Now" form:</p>
                            <img class="tutorial-img-width" src="<?= base_url() ?>assets/images/screen-14-new.jpg">
                            <p>When a job seeker applies for to a job posting they will need to fill in the Questionnaire in order to complete the application to the job.</p>
                            <p>If an employer enables the system to send Pass/Fail auto-reply emails to candidates, they will automatically receive these emails after completing the application process.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="clear"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
